<RefNameDiv>
<RefName><command>&RHNSATACT;</command></RefName>
<RefPurpose>
    activates (using an RHN Certificate) an &RHNSAT;.
</RefPurpose>
</RefNameDiv>

<RefSynopsisDiv>
<Synopsis>
    <cmdsynopsis>
        <command>&RHNSATACT; [ options <replaceable>...</replaceable> ] \
  [ --systemid<replaceable>PATH</replaceable> ] [ --rhn-cert <replaceable>PATH</replaceable> ] \
  [ --no-ssl ] [ --sanity-only ] [ --disconnected ] [ -h|--help ]</command>
    </cmdsynopsis>
</Synopsis>
</RefSynopsisDiv>

<RefSect1><Title>Description</Title>

<para>
    <emphasis>&RHNSATACT;</emphasis> activates (using an RHN Certificate) an
    &RHNSAT;. The RHN Cert is (a) checked for sanity, (b) inserted into the
    local database, and (c) inserted into the remote database.
</para>

<para>
    NOTE: activation generally occurs upon RHN Satellite installation. This
          is useful for pushing a new RHN Certificate and fixing issues related
          to account certificate issues.
</para>
</RefSect1>

<RefSect1><Title>Options</Title>
<variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>--systemid <replaceable>PATH</replaceable></term>
        <listitem>
            <para>(FOR TESTING ONLY) alternative systemid path/filename. The
                  system default is used if not specified.</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>--rhn-cert <replaceable>PATH</replaceable></term>
        <listitem>
            <para>new RHN certificate path/filename (default is
            /etc/sysconfig/rhn/rhn-entitlement-cert.xml - the saved RHN cert).</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>--no-ssl</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>(FOR TESTING ONLY) disable SSL.</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>--sanity-only</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>confirm certificate sanity. Does not activate the RHN Satellite locally or remotely.</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>--disconnected</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>activate locally, but not on remote RHN servers,</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>--ignore-expiration</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>execute regardless of the expiration of the RHN Certificate (not recommended).</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>--ignore-version-mismatch</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>execute regardless of version mismatch of existing and new certificate.<para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>-v | --verbose</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>be verbose (accumulable: -vvv means "be *really* verbose").</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>-h | --help</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>Display the help screen with a list of options.</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</RefSect1>

